      • getDocumentsFor

        public static Document[] getDocumentsFor(KeyableBean joinedBean,
                                         ILinkPropertyInfo docJoinTableLink,
                                         ILinkPropertyInfo joinedBeanJoinTableLink,
                                         IArrayPropertyInfo docJoinArrayLink,
                                         IArrayPropertyInfo joinedDocArrayLink)
        This will encapsulate the retrieval from a join table. This is expected to be referenced in an enhancement to joinedBeans type. For example Note would have this method public ABContactDocumentLink[] getDocuments() { List rtn = DocumentImpl.getDocumentsFor(this, ABContactDocumentLink.DOCUMENT_PROP.get(), ABContactDocumentLink.ABCONTACT_PROP.get(), DocumentSearchCriteria.ABCONTACT_PROP.get()); return rtn.asArray(new ABContactDocumentLink[rtn.size()]); }
        Parameters:
        joinedBean - the bean that is the opposite side of the many to many relationship
        docJoinTableLink - the Document link in the join table
        joinedBeanJoinTableLink - the link to the opposite side of the many to many relationship
        docJoinArrayLink - the array link to the joined table array in document entity
        joinedDocArrayLink - the array link to the joined table array in the joined entity
